# crible runs fully WITHOUT any of these — zero-key mode is the contract.
# The keyless core (Yahoo + audited EDGAR/FSDS/ESEF/Companies House + ECB FX)
# needs nothing here; a missing optional key just disables that one opt-in source.

# --- Free-key opt-in provider (OFF by default; the published dataset stays keyless) ---
# CRIBLE_EDINET_KEY=     # free EDINET Subscription-Key → audited Japan

# --- EDGAR fair-access (keyless, recommended) ---
# SEC asks for a declared operator + contact email. Put NO url in the value —
# the SEC WAF 403s any User-Agent containing an http(s) link.
# CRIBLE_SEC_USER_AGENT=crible you@example.com

# --- Tuning ---
# CRIBLE_BUDGET_PER_HOUR=330      # polite Yahoo request budget (NFR-007)
# CRIBLE_FETCH_TIMEOUT=60         # hard per-fetch watchdog, seconds
# CRIBLE_BOOTSTRAP_SAMPLE=AIR.PA,SAP.DE,AAPL
# CRIBLE_EDGAR_BULK=1             # weekly whole-US audited bulk in the ingest loop (~1.4 GB)
# CRIBLE_PORT=8000
